google.name: Twigs & Leaves Gallery
google.formatted_address: 98 N Main St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: This is a phenomenal gallery with many very talented artists represented.  Beautiful pottery, glass, wood, and many other gift ideas.  A must see if you are in the area.

One of my most favorite shops anywhere! I visit anytime I'm in Waynesville. The shop carries a fascinating mix of paintings, pottery, jewelry, crafted wooden pieces, textile art, and more. It's a special place.
Very helpful and knowledgeable about the jewelry in the store from local artists/jewelers.
Love this place, awesome hard to find items. Thanks

We love this place.   It is full of hand crafted goods. They have  pottery,  furniture, paintings,  jewelry and more.   If you are  in the area and like hand crafted art,  do yourself a favor and stop by.

google.name: Therapeutic Massage & Wellness Spa llc
google.formatted_address: 288 N Haywood St, Waynesville, NC 28786, USA

reviews.text: The experience was amazing. We arrived 10 minutes early for a couples massage and they took us right back. Everything was very clean and professional. Layla did an incredible job of communicating and guiding me through the whole experience. Layla‚Äôs work on a deep tissue massage was amazing. I left feeling invigorated and refreshed. I definitely will be going back.

My wife and I had a couples pregnancy massage, they were kind and gentle with my wife and left her feeling relaxed and beautiful. I too had a great experience with a deep tissue massage. Highly recommend.

Really well-managed, clean and lovely spa experience. The staff - especially Rhonda and Dana - were kind, professional and accommodating. This location offers a ton of different spa and wellness services and the prices are amazing. Highly recommend.

On my very first visit Rhonda helped me out by giving me a deep therapeutic massage. She really worked the knots out in my back and gave a lot of pressure that I needed to be able to get those spots taken care of. Thank you so much Rhonda! I look forward to visiting again real soon. So glad to have them here in Waynesville!
I would absolutely recommend! Rhonda was amazing! So professional and thorough. Helped my back pain tremendously!

google.name: World Methodist Museum
google.formatted_address: 575 N Lakeshore Dr, Lake Junaluska, NC 28745, USA

reviews.text: Very nice museum with some interesting exhibit items. Most of it is Methodist centered with a few Holy Land items. The ladies who host the museum are precious and very accommodating. I only took off a star because it is a small museum and very targeted in it's displays.
Sat outside on a bench enjoying the lake.
Very informative! There is a short video at the beginning about what you will see, but otherwise the tour is self guided.
A treasure trove of information about the Methodist Church and it's earliest days in the United States.
Wonderful informative museum.  Our Docent guide Ashley was so nice and informative. Great exhibits on Methodist beginnings along with many unique surprises!

We stopped in on Thursday traveling south this past week and were pleasantly surprised how good the food was! Our only disappointment is that they were not open on Sunday so we could visit again!   Everything was so good!  The service, the sweet tea, the rolls, tomato bisque soup (I almost ordered a to go serving, it was so good!), taco salad, chicken salad, Caroline burger and OH My Goodness the coconut cake was heavenly!!!  Top of our list of places to stop!!
The food is fabulous. Huge portions, and a great value. Service is friendly and fast.  If I'm ever in Waynesville I'll be sure to carve out a time to visit again.
